Takeaway #4: Avoid Fixed Yield

If you can't understand where the yields come from, you're the yield

Sustainable returns on cash are controlled by the FED

higher % = higher risk

The biggest example was LUNA and UST

There is no free money glitch

Many things work when money is being pumped in to the markets

Actionable Takeaway #3: Never EVER give up your keys

ü•á"Not your keys, not your coins"
ü•àSelf custody is LIFE
ü•âDeFi > CeFi

Use on/offramps with extreme caution and withdraw ASAP

Respect the decentralization-focused networks of BTC and ETH for the revolutions they are

Lesson 3: Decentralization is üëë

Bad actors cannot hide in immutable, open source code

They love CENTRALIZED environments with no oversight

Almost every failure of 2022 stemmed from Centralization 
- 3AC
- Celsius
- BlockFi
- FTX
etc

Takeaway #2: Limit Exposure to ANY single asset

Major players may be forced to dump your biggest bag if liquidated

Any altcoin could plunge 50%+ in a single day in such conditions

The only defense is to limit each alt to a small % of your portfolio and religiously take profits

Lesson 2: Hidden Leverage is Toxic

Hidden Leverage is like a landmine in the market that force big participants to DUMP and crush prices 

2022 Examples: 
- Luna Foundation dumping Bitcoin to defend UST 
- 3AC liquidated

Leverage creates forced sellers

Actionable Takeaway #1: 

ü•á Buy and Sell with the FED

When the FED "ease conditions" and stimulate the economy üëâ add more risk (stocks / coins) to your portfolio

When the FED wants to slow things down GET OUT

Simply put, "Don't fight the FED" 

The FED decided this year to slow the economy to control inflation

The results were catastrophic for asset prices

Those who respected the FED have crushed it, those who didn't got crushed

37/

So yeah, I went through some serious struggles last year

This industry can be unforgiving

But it‚Äôs also filled with relentless optimists‚Ä¶ my people

There‚Äôs nowhere in the world I‚Äôd rather be

I‚Äôm extremely grateful for everything positive and negative, I'm better for it

36/

I'm back to my explosive enthusiasm for crypto but my journey is incomplete

SuperFarm‚Äôs comeback consumes me (aka what I MUST overcome / my path to happiness)

The project is about to relaunch, benefitting from these hard earned lessons

I'm a different man now, I'm ready

35/

Finally, 

I can tell you confidently that money is NOT the source of happiness

Making money while feeling depressed and anxious is not happiness

Clout is not happiness

Real happiness comes from overcoming adversity and finding inner peace

So let‚Äôs talk about that‚Ä¶

34/

Second, I learned that quality over quantity is not just a saying

Having a ‚Äúbig‚Äù account isn‚Äôt what I thought it was

I‚Äôve adjusted to my new role now and grown in many ways from the transition

but there was a magic to that small community of OGs

I‚Äôll miss it

33/

First,

I learned that boring is better.

Going parabolic overnight was unsustainable and isn't best for anyone

The ideal strat is to launch the amazing tech near the bottom when the hype is gone

(this isn't theoretical, we are doing this)

Slow and steady growth FTW

32/

I learned some HUGE lessons from this dark episode 

They‚Äôre lessons that I will carry with me forever

Lessons that will make me a better person, better creator and better entrepreneur.

31/

Though I never took a break from work, things were slow to course correct

Getting healthy was key

Isolation from others was key

And hard work was key.

Once insulated from toxicity I worked until my eyes bled

Month by month, I felt the weight getting lighter

30/

I cut out everything I could 

I built walls around me so that I could tunnel vision and reach peak performance

and over time it worked like magic

...

It's time to discuss the comeback and lessons learned

29/

No more trading, no more editing

No more shitty foods, no more alcohol

No more reading comments

No more useless meetings

No more distractions

28/

Step 2: Limit Contact

(another form of "removal")

I shut off my calendly and changed my phone number

I was no longer ‚Äúreachable‚Äù

Most people reaching out to you are not gonna push you closer to your goals

27/

Step 1: Remove EVERYTHING not essential

I started cutting things out to get back on my feet

I expanded my research team and hired an editor

I even found a trusted third party to manage my crypto for me

Trading was far too much time and emotion on top of everything

I love crypto even if there are some rough edges

And hard as things were, people were depending on me

There was no chance of ‚Äúgiving up‚Äù 

So I made a plan to take back control

25/

Let‚Äôs pause here‚Ä¶

Love and passion for crypto culture is how I ended up in this situation

I believe in this shit, I believe in US

It‚Äôs why I wanted to make videos, and a project

why I scraped by for 3 years last bear 

24/

Meanwhile I needed to show a strong face to my team and my community 

I felt if they saw me struggling they‚Äôd think negatively about the project

I kept it all inside

But I had reached a breaking point

23/

I would internalize every negative comment

I started to get anxiety attacks

I experienced bouts of insomnia

22/

Despite everyone congratulating me on ‚Äúmy success‚Äù I did not feel successful

The pressure to deliver magic as a creator and founder was weighing heavily on me

21/

During this time things were a bit of a blur 

I was doing my best to keep up with what my viewers wanted

With what my holders wanted 

Any misstep felt like life or death

20/

People assumed: token went up so life must be peachy

It was quite the opposite

Every single day felt like a battle

19/

Everything added up and my anxiety fully boiled over

I stopped sleeping well and never left the house

I was glued to my chair

I gained tons of weight

With few exceptions, I didn‚Äôt eat lunch away from my desk for a over a year

I spent every hour fighting to create results

18

There‚Äôs some perception that if a token moons it means the founders have no worries 

This is far from the truth

The higher prices add exponential pressure to each action

I felt that weight constantly

17/

The project was launched at a tiny valuation

It was meant to be accessible and community oriented

The launch got aggressively botted and very few got to access that low val

Intentions backfired

16/

When SuperFarm launched things got 100x harder

People say crazy shit to influencers

But I was truly not prepared for how brutal people treat founders

I felt I was seeing a dark side of humanity

15/

SuperFarm was almost ready for launch

Insane hours, legal bills, dev costs, no sleep‚Ä¶

All while trying to keep up with an explosive and fast-changing ET community

14/

The comments got increasingly hostile out of the blue

Meanwhile my core community was ravenous for more content and coin picks

I felt extremely torn

Deciding what to cover to satisfy everyone was extremely difficult

13/

The new viewers were totally inexperienced

A complete guide on risk mgmt needed to somehow be compressed into EVERY episode

I hadn‚Äôt thought of what total newbs needed from my content as I had never been viral before

I had mostly existed in the dark corners of crypto land

12/

The market had changed

The times had changed

The AUDIENCE had changed 

And tbh, I was so focused on SF launch I didn‚Äôt notice the transition

11/

That January my channel experienced exponential growth

Single days were seeing more subs pour in than entire _years_ before

I thought it would make me happy, but instead I got hit with crushing anxiety

10/

2021 hit like a freight train 

It had been 3 years of day-in day-out work

Like magic, both the market and my channel erupted

9/

I started spending all my excess cash to fund an NFT farming platform (SuperFarm) inspired by DeFi summer

As BTC broke to new highs in Dec 2020, we were getting contracts audited and preparing for launch

8/

At that time everyone watching was experienced (mostly holders from the last cycle) 

They key here is that the audience was savvy

It was beautiful

We had scars from the past bull and were finally getting some gains together

7/

Out of nowhere in 2020 after YEARS of grind, my channel exploded along with DeFi summer

After thousands of hours spent, and hundreds of videos 

People started to care what I had to say

6/

No matter how bleak it looked last bear

I never took days off

I pushed myself despite most people thinking I was crazy to believe in crypto gaming

5/

Throughout this entire time, I was doing double days

Making content in the mornings

Coding games until I fell asleep

4/

For nearly 3 years I made no money from crypto youtube

I wasn‚Äôt even running ads on my videos

It was an outlet, not a business

My following was small and no one cared much what I said. I was yelling into the void. 

3/

This whole episode stems from my ambitions as a buildooor

This is the ONLY reason I did YouTube in the first place

I knew if people respected me, they would take my projects (my true ambition) seriously
